						<summary>

						<p>On a slab set up before the temple of Rāmaliṅgēśvara.</p>						

						<p>This is dated Śaka 1093, Uttarāyaṇa Saṅkrānti.</p>						

						<p>Damaged. Records the grant of a palmyragrove and a lamp-stand for burning a perpetual lamp to the god Rāmēśvara of Siripuram by Malli-Nāyaka, for the merit of his parents.</p>						

